.SH NOTES
.SS "Design Principles"
.sp
.IP "\fBCapture and share tribal knowledge\fR" 4
Installation wisdom that would otherwise live in blog posts or
"ask someone who's done it" is encoded once and shared forever \(em
with your team, your organization, or the community at large.
.IP "\fBDeclare what, not how\fR" 4
Specify package names; Lore determines the best installation method
for your platform.
.IP "\fBAugment, don't replace\fR" 4
Lore delegates to native package managers whenever possible.
Custom scripts exist for tools that need special handling.
.IP "\fBPipeline execution\fR" 4
Every deployment follows a predictable pipeline: prepare \[->] install \[->]
provision \[->] verify.
On failure, rollback executes in reverse order.
.IP "\fBNo training required\fR" 4
Package authors look at man pages, recognize Python-like Starlark syntax,
and write.
No DSL to learn; no framework to master.
